        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: Usp9X regulates spine morphology by deubiquitination of Ankyrin-G (ANK3).\n\nFigure 6: Absence of Usp9X causes persistent reduction in dendritic spine density and increase of Ankyrin-G (ANK3) ubiquitination and aggregation in mouse cortex.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Usp9X conditional knockout mice were generated by crossing Emx1-Cre heterozygous males (Iwasato et al., 2000) with Usp9XloxP/loxP female mice.\"" ;
